{# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Vitrin Quick-Checkout Dialog

   Per Zid docs (https://docs.zid.dev/themes-developer-guide
   /features/checkout-as-a-popup), including this platform template
   on the page:
     • Loads the right SDK version automatically
     • Initializes the checkout_dialog Kit Component
     • Exposes `window.checkout_dialog = { open, close }`
     • Provides `window.zid.cart.buyNow({ form_id }, opts)` for the
       Buy Now flow used by assets/js/features/buy-now.js

   That's it. Everything else (version management, Kit init, custom
   styles wiring) is handled by the platform.

   Custom styles: any per-merchant Kit customization goes through
   `window.zidCustomStyles.checkout_dialog = { ... }` set up in
   `layout.jinja` (see the existing zidCustomStyles block).
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
